  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d4b705e0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The class balance count shows that the dataset contains more benign tumors than malignant tumors, but both classes have enough examples for classification. This matters because model evaluation should not rely only on accuracy; we also need to pay attention to how well the model identifies malignant tumors.\n",
    "\n",
    "The boxplots suggest that malignant tumors tend to have higher values for radius, perimeter, area, concave points, and concavity. These features are related to tumor size and irregularity, so the separation between benign and malignant cases makes sense for this prediction task. Although there is still some overlap between the two groups, the median values for malignant tumors are consistently higher across these features. This gives us a reason to believe that classification models such as logistic regression, decision trees, and random forests may be able to predict diagnosis from the numeric measurements."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 70,
   "id": "c953d50d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Apply square root and logarithmic transformations to reduce skew in selected features\n",
    "\n",
    "def sqrt_and_log_transformations(df):\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"concavity_mean\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"concavity_mean\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"concave points_mean\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"concave points_mean\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"radius_se\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"radius_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"perimeter_se\"] = np.log(df.loc[:,\"perimeter_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"area_se\"] = np.log(df.loc[:,\"area_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"smoothness_se\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"smoothness_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"concavity_se\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"concavity_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"concave points_se\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"concave points_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"fractal_dimension_se\"] = np.sqrt(df.loc[:,\"fractal_dimension_se\"])\n",
    "    df.loc[:,\"area_worst\"] = np.log(df.loc[:,\"area_worst\"])\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "df = sqrt_and_log_transformations(df)"
   ]
