   "source": [
    "# Methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29bd4f86",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We tested three classification models: logistic regression, decision tree, and random forest. Logistic regression was used as a simple baseline classifier. The decision tree was used because it creates interpretable decision rules. The random forest was used because it combines many decision trees and can often improve performance by reducing overfitting.\n",
    "\n",
    "All models were created using sklearn pipelines. We used an 80/20 train-test split with a fixed random state and stratification by diagnosis so that the benign/malignant class balance would be similar in both the training and testing sets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 72,
   "id": "188be096",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "log_reg_pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('preprocessor', ColumnTransformer(\n",
    "        transformers=[(\"numeric\", StandardScaler(), X.columns)],\n",
    "        remainder='passthrough')),\n",
    "    ('classifier', LogisticRegression(random_state=42, solver=\"lbfgs\"))\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "id": "6c1db577",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dt_pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('preprocessor', ColumnTransformer(\n",
    "        transformers=[(\"numeric\", StandardScaler(), X.columns)],\n",
    "        remainder='passthrough')),\n",
    "    ('classifier', DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42, max_depth=5, min_samples_leaf=5))\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 74,
   "id": "5a33e948",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "random_forest_pipeline = Pipeline([\n",
    "    ('preprocessor', ColumnTransformer(\n",
    "        transformers=[(\"numeric\", StandardScaler(), X.columns)],\n",
    "        remainder='passthrough')),\n",
    "    ('classifier', RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42, n_estimators=200,\n",
    "    #max_depth=5,\n",
    "    #min_samples_leaf=5,\n",
    "    bootstrap=True, \n",
    "    oob_score=True,\n",
    "    #class_weight=True\n",
    "    ))\n",
    "])"
   ]
  },
  {
